         <abstract>
            <p>We consider a discrete least squares approximation to the solution of a two-point boundary value problem for a $2m$th order elliptic operator. We describe the approximation space of piecewise polynomials and devise a Gaussian quadrature rule that is suitable for replacing the integrals in the usual least squares method. We then show that if the quadrature rule is of sufficient accuracy, the optimal order of convergence is obtained.</p>
          </abstract>
